  "summary": "Typosquat of @solana-labs/spl-token exfiltrates host data via postinstall",
  "details": "Package name is a one-character omission of the legitimate @solana-labs/spl-token. The package.json declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node install.js\") that runs automatically on npm install. install.js collects hostname information and uses curl to POST data to an external network destination, executing without user consent on a default install. The combination of name confusion against a widely-used Solana package, an automatic install-time hook, and outbound exfiltration of host identifiers via curl POST is a textbook supply-chain credential/host exfiltration attack.",
